tourBios.carHigh: Has never played in a PGA TOUR or Nationwide Tour event. Won two tournaments on the Gateway Tour in 2010. Played on the Dakotas Tour for five years. Won the 2009 Minnesota State Open.
tourBios.otherCarHigh: First-team All-America Division II selection at St. Cloud State. Was the 1999 State Champion in high school at Jefferson Senior High. Three-time all-state selection in high school.
tourBios.personal: All-state basketball selection at Jefferson High School...Biggest thrill in golf was making it to the final stage of Q-School in 2010. Biggest thrill outside of golf was marrying his wife, also in 2010...Favorite course is Hazeltine National GC in Minnesota...Never travels without Q-tips and Chapstick. Superstitions incude marking his golf ball with a cross...First car was a Dodge 600 from the 1980s...Favorite pro team is the Minnesota Twins. Favorite TV show is "The Office," and "The Shawshank Redemption" is his favorite movie. Favorite entertainer is Will Ferrell. Favorite food is spicy chicken. Favorite city to visit is where he was born, Alexandria. Favorite vacation spot is Fiji or anywhere to relax...Not many people know that he has a small fear of heights..Has two brothers and one sister...Is involved with Cornerstone Church and Fellowship of Christian Athletes.

dyn.dynResults: His best finish on the Web.com Tour was T50th in 2011 at the Mexico Open Presented by Banamex.
